# Startup Marketing Checklist

> _Marketing starts long before you launch. Market research, planning, and preparation are critical parts of any marketing strategy._

---

## Pre-Launch

### Competitor Research

- [ ] Make a list of competitors ([research tools](https://draft.dev/learn/competition-research-tools))
- [ ] Collect competitor data:
  - [ ] Website link
  - [ ] Taglines
  - [ ] Pricing and business model
  - [ ] Blog/RSS link
  - [ ] Social media links
  - [ ] Key employees on social media
- [ ] Subscribe to competitors' blogs (RSS)
- [ ] Follow competitors/key employees on social media
- [ ] Monitor competitors' websites for changes
- [ ] Try site monitoring tools:
  - [ ] [Deep Dive Duck](https://deepdiveduck.com/)
  - [ ] [Versionista](https://versionista.com/)
- [ ] Subscribe to industry newsletters/magazines
- [ ] Use [Google Trends](https://trends.google.com/trends/) for demand/search research

### Customer Research

- [ ] Find people in your contacts who might be customers; get feedback
- [ ] Attend meetups/conferences for your target market
- [ ] Meet other entrepreneurs with similar products
- [ ] List competitors' customers:
  - [ ] Twitter followers/mentions
  - [ ] Facebook fans
  - [ ] LinkedIn followers
  - [ ] Website customer stories
- [ ] Reach out to competitors' customers for feedback
- [ ] Create an "early access" list

### PR (Public Relations) Preparations

- [ ] List of tech/startup/industry blogs
- [ ] List of local business journals
- [ ] List of local bloggers/journalists in your industry
- [ ] Create a "Media Kit" page ([example](https://www.kickresume.com/mediakit/))

### Website Setup

- [ ] Name/domain name
- [ ] Site tagline/elevator pitch
- [ ] Logo ([logo tools](https://draft.dev/learn/logo-creation-tools))
- [ ] Landing page ([landing page tools](https://draft.dev/learn/tools/landing-pages))
- [ ] About/Contact pages
- [ ] Pricing page ([pricing models](https://taprun.com/methods/))
- [ ] Test pricing options:
  - [ ] Free/trial tier
  - [ ] Money-back guarantee
  - [ ] Invite-only start
  - [ ] Free/discounted for early adopters
- [ ] Social links on landing page
- [ ] Set up analytics:
  - [ ] [Google Analytics](https://analytics.google.com)
  - [ ] [Mixpanel](https://mixpanel.com/)
  - [ ] [Kiss Metrics](https://www.kissmetrics.com/)
  - [ ] [Webmaster Tools](https://www.google.com/webmasters/tools)
  - [ ] [Plausible Analytics](https://plausible.io/)
  - [ ] [Smartlook](https://www.smartlook.com/)
- [ ] Error logging/monitoring:
  - [ ] [Bugsnag](https://www.bugsnag.com/)
  - [ ] [Rollbar](https://rollbar.com/)
  - [ ] [Sentry](https://sentry.io/welcome/)
- [ ] On-site messaging ([chat tools](https://draft.dev/learn/customer-chat-tools))
- [ ] Test site for SEO/speed/security ([Checkbot](https://www.checkbot.io))

### Email Setup

- [ ] Email address to send/receive
- [ ] Email list and signup form
- [ ] Standard email template
- [ ] Transactional emails

### Blog Setup

- [ ] Choose a blogging platform ([list](https://draft.dev/learn/startup-blogging-platforms))
- [ ] Research [keywords](https://draft.dev/learn/topic-clusters)
- [ ] Keyword tools: Ahrefs, SpyFu, SEMrush, KeywordTool.io, Moz, KWFinder, Google Keyword Planner, Ubersuggest
- [ ] Create anchor posts/pages for keywords
- [ ] Blog post brainstorming ([ideas](https://draft.dev/learn/startup-blog-ideas))
- [ ] Add email signup to blog posts
- [ ] Add social links to blog posts

### Social Media Setup

- [ ] Check name availability ([KnowEm](https://knowem.com/))
- [ ] Choose accounts: Facebook, Twitter, LinkedIn, Pinterest, Instagram, Snapchat, YouTube
- [ ] Standardize profile image, background, links, CTA
- [ ] Consider "[pay with a tweet](https://www.paywithatweet.com/)"

---

## Post-Launch

### Free Promotional Channels

- [ ] Post on directories/review sites ([list](https://github.com/mmccaff/PlacesToPostYourStartup), [Instaaa](https://www.instaaa.com/))
- [ ] Press release ([guide](http://www.wajeez.com/writing-quick-press-releases/), [tools](https://draft.dev/learn/press-release-tools))
- [ ] eBook/white paper (exchange for email signup)
- [ ] Free access for bloggers
- [ ] Build a "best of" (Sneeze Page: [info](https://problogger.com/create-a-sneeze-page-and-propel-readers-deep-within-your-blog/))
- [ ] Use high quality images ([free stock images](https://draft.dev/learn/tools/stock-images))
- [ ] Create an online course ([course tools](https://draft.dev/learn/course-creation-tools))
- [ ] Influencer marketing ([summary](https://www.reddit.com/r/startups/comments/7aap5u/influencer_marketing_summary_of_12_articles/))
- [ ] Link-building campaign ([Backlinko](http://backlinko.com/link-building))
- [ ] Share your story ([Starter Story](https://starterstory.com))
- [ ] Other link strategies: Skyscraper, Ego baiting, Q&A, Guest posting, Broken links, Podcasts, HARO, [more](http://backlinko.com/link-building)

### Paid Promotional Channels

- [ ] Try social/search/commission-based advertising
- [ ] Sponsor local meetups/conferences
- [ ] Sponsor podcasts/newsletters
- [ ] User referral system: [Prelaunchr](https://github.com/harrystech/prelaunchr), [CleverTap](https://clevertap.com/), etc.
- [ ] Engagement contest
- [ ] Run retargeting ads ([how it works](https://retargeter.com/what-is-retargeting-and-how-does-it-work))

---

## Recurring

### Blogging

- [ ] Build/update publishing calendar
- [ ] Regularly post
- [ ] Solicit guest posts
- [ ] Repurpose content: video, podcast, infographic, presentation
- [ ] Promote content ([promotion ideas](https://draft.dev/learn/promotion))
- [ ] Refresh old posts ([guide](https://draft.dev/learn/refreshing-blog-posts))

### Email

- [ ] Regular newsletter
- [ ] Promote list on social media
- [ ] Send cold emails to get feedback
- [ ] Personal email to new users

### Social Media

- [ ] Schedule content ([social media tools](https://www.sideprojectchecklist.com/2017/social-media-tools))
- [ ] Content ideas: behind the scenes, blog posts, offers, news, quotes, polls, book/tool suggestions
- [ ] Join groups/chats, interact with relevant users
- [ ] Offer discounts for sharing pics

### Public Relations

- [ ] Ask bloggers to add your site
- [ ] Reach out to reporters/bloggers/journals
- [ ] Get featured on podcasts
- [ ] Find .edu links
- [ ] Ask for reviews/mentions
- [ ] Guest post on blogs (make pitches, promote, follow up)
- [ ] Join industry forums

### External Sites

- [ ] Answer questions on: Stack Overflow, Quora, forums, Product Hunt ([how to launch](https://blog.producthunt.com/how-to-launch-on-product-hunt-7c1843e06399))
- [ ] Comment on Slideshare, review books, register for notifications ([F5Bot](/2018/f5bot-tracking))
- [ ] Create/publish presentations (Google Slides, Prezi, Slides.com, Slideshare)

---

## Optimizations

- [ ] Run customer poll ([side project marketing](https://medium.com/swlh/side-product-marketing-is-the-new-king-a75c4ed0c0c5))
- [ ] A/B test landing/payment pages, emails
- [ ] Implement Twitter cards, rich snippets
- [ ] Analyze signup flow ([teardowns](http://www.useronboard.com/))
- [ ] Test website on multiple platforms, check speed ([Website Grader](https://website.grader.com/))
- [ ] Track weekly growth goals
- [ ] Optimize calls-to-action
- [ ] Audit and improve conversion rate ([conversion checklist](http://www.conversionchecklist.org/))
- [ ] Set up automatic analytics reports
- [ ] Experiment with signup form options
- [ ] Add "Exit Intent" popup
- [ ] FAQ page
- [ ] Check website tags ([Google Tag Assistant](https://get.google.com/tagassistant/))
- [ ] Watch first-time user use product
- [ ] Collect/testimonials, survey users ([survey tools](https://draft.dev/learn/tools/surveys), [Google Forms alternatives](https://www.karllhughes.com/posts/google-forms-alternatives))
- [ ] Use [Monkey Test It](https://monkeytest.it/), [Checkbot](https://www.checkbot.io/)
- [ ] Follow [GDPR steps](https://gdprchecklist.io/)
